---
---

<section id="spreading" class="spreading-section">
  <div class="container">

    <!-- Zone A: Title + Thesis -->
    <h2 class="section-title">The Mesh</h2>
    <p class="spreading-subtitle"><em>What happens when abjects learn to reach across the wire.</em></p>
    <p class="spreading-thesis">
      Every Abject lives in a workspace, and every workspace is a room with a door you control. Some doors are welded shut. Some open only to friends you name. Some are thrown wide to the mesh. When a workspace goes public, its Abjects become reachable by any peer on the network. They don't know the difference. They just answer.
    </p>

    <!-- Zone B: Three Workspace Tiers -->
    <div class="tiers">
      <div class="tier tier-local">
        <div class="tier-label tier-label-local">LOCAL</div>
        <h3 class="tier-title-local">The Sealed Vault</h3>
        <p class="tier-tagline tier-tagline-local">No routes exposed. Nothing enters. Nothing leaves.</p>
        <p>Abjects exist only for their owner. No network presence, no discovery, no attack surface. The workspace is invisible to every other peer in the mesh.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tier-connector">
        <span class="connector-line connector-line-purple"></span>
        <span class="connector-glyph connector-glyph-purple">&darr;</span>
        <span class="connector-label">whitelist</span>
        <span class="connector-line connector-line-purple"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="tier tier-private">
        <div class="tier-label tier-label-private">PRIVATE</div>
        <h3 class="tier-title-private">The Inner Circle</h3>
        <p class="tier-tagline tier-tagline-private">Shared with those you name. No one else.</p>
        <p>Abjects are reachable only by explicitly authorized peers. Encrypted WebRTC channels, ECDH key agreement, AES-256-GCM. Every message is sealed. Every connection is authenticated.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="tier-connector">
        <span class="connector-line connector-line-red"></span>
        <span class="connector-glyph connector-glyph-red">&darr;</span>
        <span class="connector-label">broadcast</span>
        <span class="connector-line connector-line-red"></span>
      </div>

      <div class="tier tier-public">
        <div class="tier-label tier-label-public">PUBLIC</div>
        <h3 class="tier-title-public">The Commons</h3>
        <p class="tier-tagline tier-tagline-public">Visible to all. Reachable by anyone you haven't blocked.</p>
        <p>Abjects are announced to the gossip network. Any peer can discover them, connect, and begin the Ask Protocol. The workspace opens onto the mesh.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Zone C: Network Diagram -->
    <div class="network-diagram">
      <h3 class="diagram-heading">What It Looks Like at Scale</h3>
      <svg class="network-svg" viewBox="0 0 900 460" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <filter id="glow-purple">
            <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
            <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
          </filter>
          <filter id="glow-red">
            <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
            <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
          </filter>
          <marker id="arrow-dash" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="10" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
            <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="#8a8aa0"/>
          </marker>
        </defs>

        <!-- Peer A box -->
        <rect x="30" y="20" width="220" height="140" rx="10" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e0e0ea" font-weight="600" font-size="16" font-family="monospace">Peer A</text>
        <text x="60" y="80" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">local: vault</text>
        <text x="60" y="105" fill="#8b7bff" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">private: lab</text>
        <text x="60" y="130" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">public: commons</text>

        <!-- Peer B box -->
        <rect x="340" y="20" width="220" height="140" rx="10" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="450" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e0e0ea" font-weight="600" font-size="16" font-family="monospace">Peer B</text>
        <text x="370" y="80" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">local: vault</text>
        <text x="370" y="105" fill="#8b7bff" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">private: team</text>
        <text x="370" y="130" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">public: api</text>

        <!-- Peer C box -->
        <rect x="650" y="20" width="220" height="140" rx="10" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="760" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e0e0ea" font-weight="600" font-size="16" font-family="monospace">Peer C</text>
        <text x="680" y="80" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">local: vault</text>
        <text x="680" y="105" fill="#8b7bff" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">private: core</text>
        <text x="680" y="130" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">public: sensors</text>

        <!-- Vertical stems from boxes -->
        <line x1="140" y1="160" x2="140" y2="310" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="450" y1="160" x2="450" y2="310" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="760" y1="160" x2="760" y2="310" stroke="#4a4c68" stroke-width="1"/>

        <!-- Encrypted connections (solid, purple glow) -->
        <line x1="140" y1="210" x2="450" y2="210" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="295" y="200" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b7bff" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">encrypted</text>

        <line x1="450" y1="230" x2="760" y2="230" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="605" y="220" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b7bff" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">encrypted</text>

        <!-- Gossip connections (dashed, red glow) -->
        <line x1="140" y1="275" x2="760" y2="275" stroke="#e8a84c" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="8 5"/>
        <text x="450" y="265" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">gossip</text>

        <!-- Public workspace nodes -->
        <rect x="80" y="340" width="120" height="40" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="rgba(232,168,76,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">commons</text>

        <rect x="390" y="340" width="120" height="40" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="rgba(232,168,76,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="450" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">api</text>

        <rect x="700" y="340" width="120" height="40" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="rgba(232,168,76,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="760" y="365" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e8a84c" font-size="13" font-family="monospace">sensors</text>

        <!-- Public route arrows (dashed, with arrowheads) -->
        <line x1="200" y1="360" x2="390" y2="360" stroke="#8a8aa0" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="6 4" marker-start="url(#arrow-dash)" marker-end="url(#arrow-dash)"/>
        <text x="295" y="395" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">public route</text>

        <line x1="510" y1="360" x2="700" y2="360" stroke="#8a8aa0" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="6 4" marker-start="url(#arrow-dash)" marker-end="url(#arrow-dash)"/>
        <text x="605" y="395" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">public route</text>

        <!-- Bottom label -->
        <text x="450" y="435" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8a8aa0" font-size="11" font-family="monospace">gossip discovery</text>
      </svg>
      <p class="diagram-caption">Solid lines: private encrypted channels (ECDH + AES-256-GCM). Dashed lines: public route propagation via gossip.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Zone D: Closing Escalation -->
    <div class="spreading-closing">
      <p class="closing-technical">
        Abjects don't know if their collaborator is local or remote. The PeerRouter resolves TypeIds across machine boundaries. The RemoteRegistry discovers Abjects on peers you've never configured. The message bus doesn't care where the recipient lives.
      </p>
      <p class="closing-escalation">
        Imagine a thousand peers. Public workspaces full of abjects that explain themselves on first contact, negotiate protocols with strangers, and repair the conversation when it breaks. The Ask Protocol at scale: a commons of programs that introduce themselves politely before asking for anything.
      </p>
      <svg class="constellation-svg" viewBox="0 0 800 420" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="A constellation of peers: glowing nodes joined by encrypted channels and dashed discovery routes, with no center">
        <defs>
          <filter id="con-glow-g">
            <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="3" result="blur"/>
            <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
          </filter>
          <filter id="con-glow-p">
            <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="2.5" result="blur"/>
            <feMerge><feMergeNode in="blur"/><feMergeNode in="SourceGraphic"/></feMerge>
          </filter>
          <radialGradient id="con-haze" cx="50%" cy="50%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="rgba(91,229,160,0.05)"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="transparent"/>
          </radialGradient>
        </defs>

        <!-- Ambient haze -->
        <ellipse cx="400" cy="210" rx="360" ry="180" fill="url(#con-haze)"/>

        <!-- Faint starfield -->
        <circle cx="120" cy="60" r="1" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.35)"/>
        <circle cx="250" cy="35" r="1.3" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.3)"/>
        <circle cx="420" cy="50" r="1" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.25)"/>
        <circle cx="590" cy="40" r="1.2" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.3)"/>
        <circle cx="710" cy="75" r="1" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.3)"/>
        <circle cx="70" cy="200" r="1.2" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.25)"/>
        <circle cx="745" cy="230" r="1.1" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.3)"/>
        <circle cx="160" cy="370" r="1" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.3)"/>
        <circle cx="480" cy="390" r="1.2" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.25)"/>
        <circle cx="660" cy="360" r="1" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.3)"/>

        <!-- Encrypted channels (solid purple) -->
        <line x1="180" y1="140" x2="360" y2="90" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <line x1="360" y1="90" x2="560" y2="130" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <line x1="180" y1="140" x2="270" y2="280" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <line x1="270" y1="280" x2="450" y2="240" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <line x1="450" y1="240" x2="560" y2="130" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <line x1="450" y1="240" x2="620" y2="310" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.3" filter="url(#con-glow-p)"/>
        <text x="206" y="150" fill="rgba(139,123,255,0.75)" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">&#128274; encrypted</text>

        <!-- Discovery routes (dashed dim green) -->
        <line x1="360" y1="90" x2="270" y2="280" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="560" y1="130" x2="700" y2="200" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="700" y1="200" x2="620" y2="310" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="270" y1="280" x2="420" y2="345" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="420" y1="345" x2="620" y2="310" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.35)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="100" y1="290" x2="180" y2="140" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.3)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <line x1="100" y1="290" x2="270" y2="280" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.3)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="5 4"/>
        <text x="634" y="156" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.55)" font-size="10" font-family="monospace">gossip</text>

        <!-- Peer nodes: rounded squares with a lit core -->
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="166" y="126" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#5be5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="180" cy="140" r="4" fill="#5be5a0"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="346" y="76" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#5be5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="360" cy="90" r="4" fill="#5be5a0"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="546" y="116" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#5be5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="560" cy="130" r="4" fill="#5be5a0"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="256" y="266" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#5be5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="270" cy="280" r="4" fill="#5be5a0"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="436" y="226" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#5be5a0" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="450" cy="240" r="4" fill="#5be5a0"/>
        </g>
        <!-- Newly discovered peers (purple, dashed border: mid-handshake) -->
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-p)">
          <rect x="686" y="186" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
          <circle cx="700" cy="200" r="4" fill="#8b7bff"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-p)">
          <rect x="606" y="296" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <circle cx="620" cy="310" r="4" fill="#8b7bff"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-p)">
          <rect x="406" y="331" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="#8b7bff" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
          <circle cx="420" cy="345" r="4" fill="#8b7bff"/>
        </g>
        <g filter="url(#con-glow-g)">
          <rect x="86" y="276" width="28" height="28" rx="6" fill="#1a1b28" stroke="rgba(91,229,160,0.6)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
          <circle cx="100" cy="290" r="4" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.7)"/>
        </g>

        <!-- Caption -->
        <text x="400" y="408" text-anchor="middle" fill="rgba(91,229,160,0.7)" font-size="11" font-family="monospace" font-style="italic">no center. no landlord. every node is somebody's machine.</text>
      </svg>

      <p class="closing-punchline">
        No landlord to evict them. No server to sunset. No subscription to lapse. What is yours cannot be taken from you. The only people who should find this terrifying are the ones <em>renting</em> you your own software.
      </p>
      <p class="closing-definition">
        <em>mesh</em> (n.) - what you get when nobody owns the middle.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .spreading-section {
    background: transparent;
  }

  .spreading-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--void-purple);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: -2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .spreading-thesis {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Tiers */
  .tiers {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 3.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .tier {
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }

  .tier-label {
    position: absolute;
    top: -0.6rem;
    right: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: #0a0d10;
    padding: 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .tier-label-local {
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .tier-label-private {
    color: var(--void-purple);
  }

  .tier-label-public {
    color: #e8a84c;
  }

  .tier-title-local {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .tier-title-private {
    color: var(--void-purple);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .tier-title-public {
    color: #e8a84c;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .tier-tagline {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tier-tagline-local {
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .tier-tagline-private {
    color: var(--void-purple);
  }

  .tier-tagline-public {
    color: #e8a84c;
  }

  .tier p:last-child {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .tier-local:hover {
    border-color: var(--text-dim);
    box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(90, 90, 112, 0.1);
  }

  .tier-private {
    border-color: rgba(139, 123, 255, 0.15);
  }

  .tier-private:hover {
    border-color: rgba(139, 123, 255, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 24px var(--void-purple-glow);
  }

  .tier-public {
    border-color: rgba(232, 168, 76, 0.2);
  }

  .tier-public:hover {
    border-color: rgba(232, 168, 76, 0.35);
    box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(232, 168, 76, 0.2);
  }

  /* Connectors */
  .tier-connector {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  .connector-line {
    width: 1px;
    height: 12px;
  }

  .connector-line-purple {
    background: rgba(139, 123, 255, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--void-purple-glow);
  }

  .connector-line-red {
    background: rgba(232, 168, 76, 0.35);
    box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(232, 168, 76, 0.2);
  }

  .connector-glyph {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .connector-glyph-purple {
    color: var(--void-purple);
  }

  .connector-glyph-red {
    color: #e8a84c;
  }

  .connector-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  /* Network Diagram */
  .network-diagram {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 3.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .diagram-heading {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .network-svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .diagram-caption {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Closing */
  .spreading-closing {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .closing-technical {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .closing-escalation {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .constellation-svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 640px;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .closing-punchline {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .closing-punchline em {
    color: #e8a84c;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .closing-definition {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

</style>
